title: "Output Language Effect on AI-Assisted Software Engineering: A Pilot Study with Claude Opus 4.7"
message: "If you use these results, please cite as below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - family-names: Miyoshi
    given-names: Shuji
    affiliation: Sports AI Science
date-released: 2026-05-15
keywords:
  - llm
  - claude
  - software-engineering
  - empirical-study
  - language-effect
  - ai-assisted-development
license: MIT
abstract: >
  A pilot empirical study (N=3 per language group, parallel sub-agent design)
  measuring how Claude Code's output language choice (English vs Japanese)
  affects QCD — Quality, Cost, Delivery — when building the same specified
  software (a 10-AC scientific calculator). Includes a System Dynamics model
  used to generate pre-registered hypotheses, the parallel orchestration
  methodology, complete agent artifacts, and rigorous statistical analysis
  (Welch's t, Mann-Whitney U, Cliff's δ, bootstrap CI, power analysis).
